cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.DC 

The paper discusses the integration of systems engineering and disciplines studying complex systems in nature or society, which suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY), computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE), social and information networks (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The specific case study of transportation networks also suggests a potential fit with computer science and engineering (cs.CE) and optimization and control (cs.SY).
